column5: Went for a couple hours today and talked to a few friends and reps. Really looking forward to the new megabass presence in USA/Canada. Will be going Monday again, will be wearing my jersey too.

Just got back a little while ago. Same ol same ol, but hey I enjoy it, gets me dreamin of some soft water days ahead. Sat and watched a fellow talk about some Mizmo soft baits..I think thats what there called and some oil and chap stick scent stuff for your lures. Actually enjoyed listening to him (forget his name)and talked fishing with him after his presntation. Overall a great way to kill a few hours and check out whats new.

My son and I went from 430 to 830.  I hope the vendors were busy during the day because it was dead when we were there.  Not complaining about the lack of crowds though.  Enjoyed the show and spoke to some very nice lodge owners and boat sales people.   My son got a rod and reel and a few lures from the 3 for $10 bin.

It was good.... i mean i got to see a;ot of peple i only get to see occasionally... got a fantastic deal on some rain jackets...  really ya gotta go see those guys.  Marks work wearhouse stuff at 1/2 the price! Lures and tours and maybe even convinced the wife to look at a trailer fo some travels next year.  great day for me.  gonna spend tomorrow on younge street and a nice suite and take a break from email and the phone.  why the heck was everyone hugging my wife???
Same reason you do
make sure if you go to the show to stop in at the anglers choice booth!!
I really wish I could go tommorow or sunday however I'm at the residence at the corner of 404 and FInch with no vehicle and it would cost a fortune/take an eternity to get there by bus lol.
Ill be there for the afternoon on friday!  Who else is going this weekend??

Well I might try to visit on Friday but I may have to trade that for a pass to fish Saturday on Nipissing. Although my wife does have tickets to Bon Jovi on Sunday so I might get both tripsâ€¦ lets see how Thursday goes and I'll know more.
will be there monday for the show and bass talk
Clinic visits Friday. Hoping to get there during the weekend.
You have an extra ticket?  I was going Sunday or Monday,but can be nudged for friday noon
Hopefully late Friday afternoon if work dosent get in my way. Fortuneatly I work down the street.
Going Friday afternoon as well. Last year there were some good deals on trolling motors. There was also a small booth that had some good rod and reel prices.
I'm closing the shop down at moon and taking a few of the guys. ( I call it team building so I can expense the tickets and lunch) does kennedy's still serve lunch?
As always,you see this,say Hi.
Unfortunately, work gets in the way, as usual!!
Would like to get out to a show since its been a few years but I seem to be able to find what I need (Fishing Related) to buy and research on line and plum outta money because of it. Maybe next year.

Will be there on Saturday all day...Booth working and working the sponsors.. Doing the kids fishing Derby again.. so got to work the sponsors.. Already got Rapala & Pure fishing.. Lucky Strike..True Canadian Outdoors use to be (Fishontario) till they moved... come see me at their Booth for a chat???or take me for a  cold one..

I have the kids this weekend, so I doubt I'll be able to go, I stopped taking them a couple years ago they just don't enjoy it as much as I do. haha I'll ask them as I always do so who knows maybe on sunday. Its a pricey affair though for me to get down there with a mit full of kids.
i will be headed down on saturday with the wife and baby. should be fun
I'll be fishing.
Stay out of the Kids Pond
I already bought my marshmellows and trebles!!   Ah well, I'll sell them to some Russian dude on the Credit I guess.
Ive got Family day at the show.... SOOO looking forward to it..No wife, no kids.....just a fun time out
I should be there sometime this weekend, not sure when.
I"m going Friday.  In the market for a new boat!
I'll be coming down in a couple hours, say hi if you see me!
Well I went,I saw,and waited for a cold one with ya,but didnt see ya TJ. seen Dan and met Ryan. Did the hour and a bit walk around,left with a bunch of dry flies. Think I,ll drown my sorrows now.
ill be there sunday morn.....if anyone needs a pair of free tickets...pm me and we will meet at the front door...
Heading down Saturday with my Father & Monday with 3 or 4  buddies for the Bass Talks, I'll be in my CBAF Shirt & Shorts, got to show off my Bass Tattoes, lol Tight Lines SBK
Me.
